fields.body: I have recently graduated from the Department of Computer Science at the University of Sheffield with First Class Honours in Software Development for Business. I enjoy working as part of agile teams on full stack solutions for clients. I have commercial experience in a number of languages and frameworks including Django; the Python framework upon which this website is based.

• Agile Development & Scrum
  • Continuous Integration
  • Micro-service designs and containerization with Docker
  • Cross Functional Teams
  • Cross Browser Testing & Debugging
  • Mobile-First, Responsive Design

• Away from work and education I am a keen footballer and used to be part of the Computer Science team.
  • In the summer i can usually be found attempting to get around a golf course in less than 100 strokes. 
  • I also volunteer as a leader at Scouts and have been fortunate enough to take part in activities such as white water rafting and abseiling.

• Academic Achievement Scholarship - University of Sheffield
  • Outstanding Refereeing Achievement - FA

fields.label: tesco_mobile
fields.information: Work as a software developer as part of the DevOps team using agile methodologies. Responsibilities include designing and developing new features, building new micro-services and maintaining existing infrastructure. Tools used include Python, PHP, Docker, JavaScript, Java, Go and more

fields.label: uni
fields.information: Work alongside lecturers in first year lab classes to demonstrate 'Ruby programming and Git'. The role included helping students with questions they have as they complete lab sheets set by the lecturer and ensuring they do not communicate in formal assessments.

fields.label: hp
fields.information: Working with another intern I produced a reporting tool for the Accelerated life testing team. We liaised with the customer to gather requirements, designed the solution and implemented it using web technologies including PHP, HTML and JavaScript. Then created automated unit and feature tests before releasing the system to a Linux production server. I attended sync-up meetings, using Skype, with other members of the team, some of whom were based in India and the US.

fields.label: uni
fields.information: I have recently graduated from the Department of Computer Science at the University of Sheffield with First Class Honours in Software Development for Business. I was accepted into the university on an academic achievement scholarship.

fields.label: highdown
fields.information: I completed my GCSE's and A-levels here. I was also Head Boy for a year which involved providing a voice for the students in meetings with senior leadership and also public speaking.  A levels: Computing(A), Maths(A), Geography(A), Physics AS(B). 11 GCSEs(A*-B) including Maths(A*), Computing(A*)
